 You do not want to have group members know you are a part of a certain guild - which would be pointless because if they wanted to know all they would have to do is a &quot;Guildstatus&quot;<br><br> 4&gt; If you are in Afterlife, and you get sick of people from other servers coming in, doing a /who all afterlife and asking about 60 questions to how to do things in the game. <br><br><br>Other than this what is the point? If you are trying to hide where your guild is at, you can easily do /role. No one will be able to tell which zone you are in and you will still show the guild you are in. <br><br>If you are trying to hide your class to not get bothered for GG's, resses, etc - you can do /role and still show your tag but not your class. Again - no point for hiding your guild tag itself. <br><br>I have asked a couple people why they hide their guild tag, being that the majority of thisguild which shall remain nameless, always has about half of its members in /Anon and not /role. I have gotten no answer or simply &quot;Because I like /anon /role &quot; ?? When I would ask why no answer. I would ask, &quot;All you are doing is hiding your guild tag - ashamed to be in that guild?&quot;. <br><br>So anyone out there reading - please tell me why people would want to hide their guild tag from other than any of the following reasons. Because the way I see it: <br><br>1&gt; You are hiding from your own guild members. Why the hell would you want to do that?  If they ever asked you for anything tell them you are busy and be honest. Why the need to hide?<br><br>2&gt; You are in Afterlife and do it simply because they get people from all walks of life logging in to ask them questions about how to kill shit. <br><br>3&gt;  You are hoping someone doesn't do a /guildstatus to see which guild you are in, and will group with you or GG/TL you anyhow. <br><br>So what are the reasons for the /anon command which you cannot get the same results with /role but still wear yo