ild tags? </span><hr size=1> I know when I was in my previous guild I went /anon a lot.  Mainly because I would get questions in the middle of raiding.  I don't mind answering questions, but not in the middle of a raid.  <br><br>For some reason, when people want to ask a question, they look for a high level person in a strong guild - so you are more likely to get newbie tells.  I still don't understand why that is, but I guess the assumption is that someone in a strong guild has done more and has more experience with stuff (which I don't happen to think is true, but that's my guess as to why we get a lot of newbie tells)<br><br>/who all rogue 60<br><br>They will generally pick someone from that list - to send a tell.  I just want to be off that list if I am busy =)<br><br>I don't mind answering tells if I am just out xping, but not during a raid =) As for the /role vs.  /anon - I personally don't like pink, so I generally use /anon =p<br><br>That's my reason =) <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68709 > <b> <i>Kalynn Taranis</a> </B></i><BR><b>Assassin for Hire</b><BR><i> Mithaniel Marr </i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFE4E1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ustormwynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormwynd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#D87093>(1/28/02 10:26:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why do players hide their guild tags? </span><hr size=1> Haha i remember doing that back when i was in a guild just for the hell of being able to not be confused with any tremoil going on at the moment.  The other times i went anon