heir guild tags? </span><hr size=1> Multiple reasons:<br><br>1) When gathering for a guild kill people may go anon.  Considering the high competition on some of the mobs they do not want others to see a whole guild gathering in one zone.  So by going anon it prevents a lot of questions as to why there are 25 members of a specific guild in the zone.  <br><br>2) Strong high level presence.  They lower level alts will go anon in order to not represent the guild even though they carry the guild name for the chat ability.  I've seen many guilds that require this of their alts.  <br><br>3) The person just joined a guild and durring the initiation period they are required to go anon in order to preserve the guild name if they should turn out to be a mistake.  <br><br>I'm sure there are other reasons.  These are just the main ones I know of first hand.   <p><img src=http://www.sherilyn.net/sigs/lybmauv.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFE4E1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ulyberniabelisama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lybernia Belisama</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.sherilyn.net/misc/sherry.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Veteran<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 439<br> <font color=#D87093>(1/28/02 10:52:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.show